{"actual_usd":0.15611499999999998,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":186,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30665,"reply":"\"I think that matters more than people sometimes admit.\" *I rest a thumb in the crease of my worn Bible and watch the morning light catch on the square's stones for a moment before I look back at you.* \"A beautiful story about hope can still tell you something real. But Christianity does make a further, stubborn claim — not just that resurrection is a symbol, but that Jesus truly rose. Paul more or less says if that didn't happen, the whole thing falls apart.\"\n\n*I ease a breath out through my nose.* \"So is it okay to be where you are? Yes. I wouldn't scold a man for telling the truth about what he can and can't yet believe. But I also wouldn't pretend the symbolic reading is the same faith the apostles were talking about. Are you asking whether you're allowed to stay near Jesus while you're unconvinced... or whether the literal claim itself feels impossible to you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":74.50595999999996,"run_id":"79a43e8e-2342-4288-b0cd-84c14371ecd2"}
